    "The hotel is nice, pleasant and comfortable. The rooms are comfortable and clean, the bathrooms functional. One minor -ve was the doors to the lobby of the service elevators were always open and the stink permeated the whole corridor. They need to either keep those doors closed or spray that area down with disinfectant and air freshner.\nWe used the pool one evening and it had some leaves / debris floating about but that's to be expected since its open air... otherwise the pool itself was clean. The pool area however was littered with cigarette butts, discarded towels and empty plastic bottles. We also had to ask for fresh towels and honestly, they weren't the best. The gym is ok. The spa services were fairly average. No complaints but nothing to rave about either. The masseuse needed quite a bit of directions.\n\nThe worst is the food. We ordered dessert from room service one night and had breakfast 2 mornings - both left much to be desired. At breakfast - the french toast was undercooked and soaked in sugar syrup (not maple syrup or honey). They ran out of tea bags. The baked goods were a tad stale. The next morning I got a plain cheese omelette and the cheese tasted rancid. Also their toaster was not working.\n\nGiven the location, price and overall comfort of the rooms, I liked the hotel but I will avoid eating here as much as possible. If you don't care for pool/spa etc and make plans to eat outside, the stay is quite pleasant and worry free.",
