    "Visited this lovely hotel in Dec 19 with my family. The hotel is located bang opposite Pune railway station withing walking distance. I've stayed at several Lemon Tree properties in the past and this one like the rest doesn't fail to impress. Clean rooms with great hospitality is what makes the brand unique. They have a variety of add ons like late/early check ins etc. Don't expect this brand to be in the league of a Westin or a Marriott. However all said and done this place is a bang for one's buck. We got an upgrade to a higher floor and the rooms were way better than what we asked for. Since we are on a Modified American Plan, we opted for dinner at their Coffee shop called Citrus. Honestly the dinner was very mediocre , however for the price that we paid, it was worth it. Breakfast on the contrary was a treat. The staff were all extremely hospitable and made the kids feel at home. The property has a full fledged gym and an open air swimming pool on the lower floor. They have a lounge has well that offers a liquid buffet (unlimited alcohol at a fixed price). Since the property is so centrally located, travelling is very convenient. The kids really enjoyed their stay and I'm guessing that says it all.",
